issue.body:
$2000 USD Bounty here!

If you can find a nice solution to our local dev experience, take home a $2000 USD bounty. We have a very strong feeling the culprit is the App Store. The problem is that refactoring it is a challenge since we have 100+ apps, there are tons of circular dependencies and our `main` branch is constantly merged to, making conflicts hard to work around.

Take these PRs as inspiration to ideally not load the entire App Store upon any given page load in our app. If you debug locally and watch what happens in the `.next/server/chunks` folder, you will see it's compiling a ton of code that's not needed.

These PRs have gotten close but refactoring the test suite to continue passing has been quite a blocker.

https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/pull/22450
https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/pull/19771

Current initial page load times per page even on a beast MacBook Pro can be upwards of 10-12s. **This needs to be cut by at least 80%.**

pull_request.title: Fix module loading in logging config
pull_request.body:
## Summary

Fix issue where custom logging configuration with simple module paths (like `log_config.LOGGING_CONFIG`) caused triggerer and scheduler to fail during startup.

## Problem

When users set `logging_config_class = log_config.LOGGING_CONFIG` in their `airflow.cfg`, the `load_logging_config()` function would fail because:

1. `logging_class_path.rsplit(".", 1)[0]` produces `"log_config"`
2. `import_string("log_config")` fails because it expects a dot-separated path like `"module.submodule.attribute"`
3. This caused `ImportError` and prevented `REMOTE_TASK_LOG` and `DEFAULT_REMOTE_CONN_ID` from being loaded
4. In some environments, this prevented triggerer and scheduler from starting

## Solution

Replace `import_string()` with `importlib.import_module()` in `load_logging_config()`

## Changes

### Code
- in`airflow-core/src/airflow/logging_config.py`, with`load_logging_config()`

### Test
- in `airflow-core/tests/unit/core/test_logging_config.py`
- **Added**: Parametrized test for different module path structures
- **Added**: Test for graceful fallback when remote logging vars are missing
- **Added**: Helper method to reduce test code duplication

## Related Issues

resolves #54414

comment.body:
Same sort of issue here with HW transcoding. I've got old AVI format with MPEG 4 layer2. Using software decoding. But hardware encoding to h264.

The immich_server container logs shows executing this command:
```
fmpeg -n 10 /usr/bin/ffmpeg -init_hw_device vaapi=accel:/dev/dri/renderD128 -filter_hw_device accel -i /mnt/input.AVI -y -c:v h264_vaapi -c:a aac -movflags faststart -fps_mode passthrough -map 0:0 -map_metadata -1 -map 0:1 -g 256 -v verbose -vf hwupload=extra_hw_frames=64 -compression_level 7 -qp:v 23 -global_quality:v 23 -rc_mode 1 /data/encoded-video/output.mp4
```
resulting in error message:
```
....
[out#0/mp4 @ 0x2c6c0292880] Starting thread...
[h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c0211580] Failed to end picture encode issue: 6 (invalid VASurfaceID).
[h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c0211580] Encode failed: -5.
[vost#0:0/h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c00d2580] Error submitting video frame to the encoder
[vost#0:0/h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c00d2580] Error encoding a frame: Input/output error
[vost#0:0/h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c00d2580] Task finished with error code: -5 (Input/output error)
[vost#0:0/h264_vaapi @ 0x2c6c00d2580] Terminating thread with return code -5 (Input/output error)
[vf#0:0 @ 0x2c6c0150b80] All consumers returned EOF
[vf#0:0 @ 0x2c6c0150b80] Terminating thread with return code 0 (success)
...
```

When I run this command manually I get the same error.
However, when I change the -vf parameter.
`-vf hwupload=extra_hw_frames=64`
to
`-vf format=nv12,hwupload=extra_hw_frames=64`
it all converts like a charm.

So would it be possible to maybe let us add 'additional' parameters to Hardware Acceleration section?

pull_request.body:
### Summary

If a list's comparison function calls array.clear() and gc.collect() during sort, an element slot can become MP_OBJ_NULL. Guard mp_obj_get_type() to avoid a NULL dereference and raise a proper exception instead of crashing.

Closes: #17941

### Testing

Tested on Unix port.

**Automated Reviews**: Continuous reviews of the pull requests including incremental commits.

issue.title: perf: Performance Optimization Phase 2 - Partytown, Self-hosted Fonts & Bundle Splitting #367
issue.body:
## 🚀 Performance Optimization Phase 2

This PR implements several critical performance optimizations identified in issue #367 to improve site performance and reduce bundle size.

### ✅ Implemented Optimizations

#### 1. **Partytown Integration** 
- Moved Cloudflare Analytics to web worker using Partytown
- Prevents main thread blocking from third-party scripts
- Updated both BaseLayout and MobileOptimizedLayout

#### 2. **Self-Hosted Fonts**
- Eliminated Google Fonts CDN dependency
- Self-hosting Inter (400, 500, 600) and Playfair Display (400, 500, 600)
- Added font preloading for critical fonts
- Reduced 2+ network requests to external domains

#### 3. **Advanced Bundle Splitting**
- Enhanced Rollup configuration with feature-based chunks
- Separate chunks for: portfolio, contact, about, navigation features
- Split vendor bundles: react, framer-motion, icons, turnstile
- Better code organization for lazy loading

#### 4. **Component Optimization**
- Created Astro version of YouTubeEmbed component
- Prepared for future React → Astro conversions

### 📊 Expected Performance Impact

- **Reduced Main Thread Blocking**: Analytics run in web worker
- **Faster Font Loading**: No external font requests, preloaded critical fonts
- **Smaller Initial Bundle**: Better code splitting with feature-based chunks
- **Improved LCP**: Reduced render-blocking resources

### 🔍 Testing Checklist

- [ ] Fonts load correctly (no FOUT/FOIT)
- [ ] Analytics still track properly
- [ ] Bundle splitting works as expected
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Mobile performance improved
- [ ] Lighthouse score improvement

### 📈 Metrics to Monitor

- Bundle size reduction (target: <350KB from current 508KB)
- Lighthouse score improvement (target: 90+ from current 60-70)
- LCP improvement
- Reduced network requests

### 🔗 Related Issues

Fixes part of #367 (Performance Optimization Phase 2)

### 📝 Notes

- Font files are now committed to the repository (138KB total for all 6 font files)
- Partytown adds minimal overhead (~5KB) but significantly improves main thread performance
- Future optimizations can build on this foundation

### Next Steps (Not in this PR)

- Setup performance budget enforcement
- Add Lighthouse CI to GitHub Actions
- Create AnimateOnScroll Astro component
- Convert more React components to Astro where possible
